arb4j (1.1.1) UNRELEASED; urgency=low

  [ Stephen Crowley ]
  * σ-table exponential eliminated (#1034). The cyclic {σ,α,β,h} OPS
    recurrence in MuntzPadeApproximant is now memoized through σfunc and
    warmed bottom-up (ops.warmTo(m, bits)) before any top-down read, so a
    top-down evaluation can no longer memoize a partial-∅ entry and then
    divide by it. Re-calls land as cache hits and the previous exponential
    re-computation of the σ-table is gone (~13× on the affected paths).
  * New arb.functions.IndexCache<C>: O(1) memoization keyed by a signed int,
    backed by two on-demand-growing ArrayLists (a non-negative side and a
    negative side). It replaces the TreeMap<Integer,C> peek/poke cache whose
    arb.Integer.compareTo comparator path dominated recursive-sequence
    profiles and which allocated a fresh arb.Integer key on every poke.
    Function.peek/Function.poke retarget to it, and it serves the negative
    recurrence indices the earlier single-ArrayList cache returned null for.
    Generated classes now carry an IndexCache `cache` field, clear it on
    invalidateCache, and copy it into nested function instances.
  * Context.invalidateAllCaches() walks every instantiated function and clears
    its per-index cache. Those caches are precision-blind — an entry built at
    N bits is accurate to N bits and no further — so MuntzPadeApproximant
    invalidates and rebuilds when more bits are requested while reusing the
    cache as-is for fewer-or-equal bits.
  * MuntzPadeFunctional: cachedOrder dropped from the evaluate memo key (now
    keyed on (v, bits)); invalidateCache uses the alreadyInvalidated.add()
    short-circuit and propagates invalidation to the Müntz coefficient
    sequence a.
  * Generated close()/field-descriptor fixes (#1034): emitted close() reads
    each function-reference field through its declared interface descriptor
    (GETFIELD), CHECKCASTs to AutoCloseable and INVOKEINTERFACEs close() to
    match the bytecode declareFunctionReferences emits; the context field is
    loaded via internalName() so packaged/namespaced contexts resolve.
  * #1032 cleanup: deduplicated the instantiate() re-entrance guards and
    trimmed the surrounding comments on the self-recursive-instance machinery.
  * Tooling: bin/profile, a JFR-based hot-method profiler for main classes
    and tests.
  * Licensing: add License.txt and a Production Use License contract template
    (ProductionUseLicense.template.txt) conveying copyright and patent terms.
  * Docs: CACHING-MECHANISM.md writes up the index-cache / σ-table warming
    design. New regression tests SigmaTableCacheEfficiencyTest (HITS/MISSES
    accounting, guarded against a vacuous zero-access pass) and IndexCacheTest.
  * Issues addressed: #1032, #1034.

 -- Stephen Crowley <stephencrowley214@gmail.com>  Fri, 22 May 2026 14:35:07 -0500

arb4j (1.1) UNRELEASED; urgency=low

  [ Stephen Crowley ]
  * Müntz–Padé spectral tau method for the constant-coefficient fractional
    Riccati equation Đᵅ y = p(v) + q(v)·y + r(v)·y², landing the machinery
    behind the rough-Heston characteristic-function publication (tag
    v1.0-rh-publication) and beyond. RiccatiMuntzPadeFunctional builds the
    curried Müntz coefficient sequence k ↦ v ↦ aₖ(v) from the algebraic
    recurrence and hands it to MuntzPadeApproximant for global analytic
    continuation by diagonal Padé approximation.
  * MuntzPadeApproximant rebuilt around the polynomial Chebyshev/Wheeler
    σ-table OPS recurrence (#1031, #1016), replacing the Hankel
    bordered-inverse construction — O(M²) and free of Hankel
    ill-conditioning. The arbitrary M<1024 expansion cap is removed; the
    expansion order is chosen adaptively per evaluation point and requested
    precision (#1010) rather than from a fixed sample point, with a
    precision guard so cache reuse can never cap accuracy and a Padé
    precision-floor detector replacing DivisionByZeroException catching.
  * MuntzPadeFunctional memoizes its most-recent evaluate result and returns
    it again for a repeated (v, order, bits), cleared on invalidateCache so a
    parameter refresh can never surface a stale approximant.
  * FractionalRicattiOrthogonalPolynomialMomentFunctionalSequence (renamed
    from OrthogonalPolynomialFractionalRiccatiMomentFunctionalSequence)
    exposes the OPS of the Müntz–Padé moment functional via the polynomial
    Chebyshev/Wheeler recurrence; shared Context is threaded through so the
    moment sequence m's expression survives, and p/q/r registration in
    RiccatiMuntzPadeFunctional is idempotent.
  * HyperbolicTangentTest pins tanh as a fractional-Riccati-moment-problem
    oracle (P=1, Q=0, R=−1, μ=1); five tanh oracle cases now pass.
  * Expression-compiler / codegen hardening: self-recursive sequences use a
    separate instance per recursion level with the attendant codegen defects
    fixed (#1032); referenced-function ASM owners route through
    Expression.internalName() at every emit site (#1024); scalarCoDomain maps
    polynomial-sequence interfaces to their element type (#1021); the
    f(x)/g(x) → 1 fold and a WhenNode lookup-switch type-promotion bug are
    fixed; ClassCircularityError avoided by caching the compiled class under
    its simple name; lambdas are no longer registrable as functions.
  * Added Complex.neg(Complex result) and RealPolynomial composition with
    expression-compiler coverage; documented the solution methodology for
    constant-coefficient fractional Riccati equations.
  * Issues addressed: #1005, #1010, #1014, #1015, #1016, #1018, #1021, #1023,
    #1024, #1027, #1029, #1031, #1032. Test suite 838/838 green on JDK 26.

