arb4j (0.99.9.9.10) UNRELEASED; urgency=low

  [ Stephen Crowley ]
  * StationaryGaussianProcessSampler PSD pipeline runs end-to-end in
    arb precision. powerSpectralDensity, theoreticalPowerSpectralDensities,
    frequencies, and positiveFrequencies are arb.Real vectors instead of
    double[]. computePowerSpectralDensity, generateFrequencies,
    getPowerSpectralDensity, and getKernel take/return Real instead of
    double[]. The double cast happens only at the chart-feeding edge,
    where doubleValue() per cell goes into DoubleDataSet. Subclasses
    BandLimitedWhiteNoiseSampler and RandomWaveSampler updated to the
    new signatures. ingestPrecomputedSamplePath fixed to read the path
    from samplePath.re() (it was reading .im() which is always zero in
    the path-based pipeline). Tests 816/816 green. Headless smoke run
    via bin/snapshot arb.applications.RandomWaveSampler confirms the
    PSD chart still renders the empirical scatter on top of the
    theoretical 1/(π√(1−f²)) curve inside [0,1] and the covariance
    chart still tracks J₀(2πt).
  * PSD chart draws the asymmetric χ²_2 interquartile-range bar per bin
    as an indicative confidence whisker. populatePowerSpectralDensityDatasets
    builds an asymmetric RealDataSet for the empirical curve: ln(1+Ŝ) goes
    into re().getMid(), the +error distance ln(1+Ŝ/0.7213) − ln(1+Ŝ) into
    re().getRad(), the −error distance ln(1+Ŝ) − ln(1+Ŝ/3.4759) into
    im().getRad(). The IQR (50% interval) is wide enough to be readable
    yet narrow enough not to saturate the chart, ~50x narrower than the
    full 95% CI. The 95% CI is the true uncertainty of the unsmoothed
    periodogram but is too wide to render usefully without smoothing.
    New helper newPeriodogramErrorBarRenderer installs an
    ErrorDataSetRenderer with ErrorStyle.ERRORBARS so chartfx queries
    the dataset's DataSetError surface for asymmetric whiskers. Marker
    size on the empirical dataset bumped down to 2 so the bars stay
    visually dominant.
  * PSD chart and Random White Noise Measure chart x-axes default to
    [0, +nyquistFrequency] (the non-negative half of the spectral
    support) since the periodogram of a real-valued process is
    symmetric about zero. A "Show negative frequencies" checkbox in
    the top control bar (next to "Sample length L") toggles both
    charts simultaneously to the full {@link #spectralSupport}.
    Implementation: shared protected configureFrequencyAxis(XYChart),
    shared boolean field showNegativeFrequencies. Charts.createGridPane
    grew a (charts, covarianceWrapper, psdWrapper) overload, kept
    backward-compatible with the existing 1- and 2-arg forms.
  * Tests 816/816 green throughout. RandomWaveSampler smoke screenshot
    confirms bars draw and the negative-frequency toggle flips both
    charts together.
  * Modal progress dialog wraps every long-running computation in a
    StationaryGaussianProcessSampler subclass: the initial sample-path
    generation on start(), the resize handler driven by Sample length L
    Apply, and the autocorrelation Refresh handler. New classes
    arb.viz.ProgressDialog and arb.viz.ProgressReporter; new helper
    runWithProgress(Stage, String, Consumer<ProgressReporter>) on the
    parent. The worker runs on a daemon Thread, ticks the dialog's
    ProgressBar, and checks isCancelled() between iterations. Cancel
    aborts cleanly without mutating chart data. The dialog is auto-
    dismissed on completion; the user can close it early via the Cancel
    button. Threading split: heavy arb arithmetic on the worker, all
    XYChart construction and dataset mutation marshalled to the FX
    thread via Platform.runLater. The seed-based pipeline
    (generateSamplePathFromSpectrallyColoredOrthogonalRandomMeasure)
    ticks the reporter at five coarse stages with a setMessage status
    string at each. The path-based pipeline
    (InverseShiftedPhasePullbackSampler.prepareSamplePath) ticks per
    bin from its existing AtomicLong counter. Tests 816/816 green.
  * RealDataSet implements ChartFX DataSetError so the default
    ErrorDataSetRenderer draws error bars without a custom renderer.
    Two error modes chosen at construction:
      - symmetric (default): y row is a Real vector; the cell radius is
        the single error magnitude reported on both sides;
      - asymmetric: y row is a Complex vector; re().getMid() = value,
        re().getRad() = +error distance, im().getRad() = -error distance,
        im().getMid() unused.
    Public API preserved end-to-end: getRealXValues, getRealYValues,
    getValues, getTimes, getResolution, get, getDataCount, structure,
    close, toString, set keep their existing signatures and semantics.
    New: getComplexYValues (asymmetric only), getPositiveErrorValues,
    getNegativeErrorValues, isAsymmetric, plus the three DataSetError
    methods. The internal RealMatrix data field is gone; storage is one
    Real x vector plus either a Real or Complex y vector. Error
    magnitudes are zero by default; the periodogram chi-squared interval
    will be wired into them in a follow-up.
  * Magnitude vector grows an element-array view: Magnitude[] elements,
    set(int, Magnitude), and an elements-aware get(int). Mirrors the
    Real/Complex element-array vector pattern used by Complex.getReal().
    No FLINT vector op is called on Magnitude vectors, so contiguity is
    not required.
  * Real.rad() returns a strided Magnitude view over the radii of a Real
    vector. dim == 1 returns getRad() directly; dim > 1 lazily builds an
    element-array Magnitude whose get(i) aliases this.get(i).getRad().
    No copy. Cached.
  * DEVELOPING.md and README.md: bump JDK version from 25 to 26 to match
    the pom and CLAUDE.md.
  * MuntzPadeFunction is a ComplexFunctional<Complex,Complex,ComplexFunction>:
    v becomes the input parameter to evaluate, not a mutable field.
    RiccatiMittagLefflerFunction extends MuntzPadeFunction; v field and
    muntzCoefficientsAtV are gone. The curried Muntz coefficient sequence
    a:k➔v➔a_k(v) is built once in the Context using a forward-declared
    mutually-recursive cluster (a, S) so the integer memo on k fires at
    every v without recompilation. New top-level MuntzPadeApproximantAtV
    holds the per-v Pade pair built lazily inside evaluate.
  * Issue #994: Re-entrancy guard on Expression.compile() ends the
    recompile cascade in mutually-recursive curried sequence clusters.
    A peer's generateFunctionInitializer at line 2609 forced
    nestedExpression.compile() when variablesDeclared was false; for
    a ⇔ S where each references the other through a curried
    ComplexFunctionSequence (k➔v➔body), this re-entered compile()
    on an Expression whose generateFunctionalElement had already
    consumed its placeholderVariable, producing an inner functional
    Expression with independentVariable=null and crashing splice with
    UndefinedReference 'v'. compileInProgress flag short-circuits the
    re-entrant call; the outer compile's symbolic class-name reference
    in bytecode is resolved at JVM-load time when the recursive
    compile chain has finished. Test
    SelfRecursiveCurriedSequenceTest covers self-recursive and
    mutually-recursive curried sequence cases.
  * Universal lazy ∂/∂v on every Expression-compiled Function. Function
    grows derivative(VariableReference) and derivative(String) defaults;
    Expression.derivative(VariableReference) does pure-Java AST surgery
    via deepCloneExpression + rootNode.differentiate(probe).simplify
    with no source re-parsing; every generated class now emits
    getExpression() returning a back-pointer field populated at
    instantiate() time so the default reaches the source AST. Per-name
    partialDerivativeCache memoizes compiled partials.
  * Function gains a Jacobian class and jacobian(String[]/
    VariableReference[]/VariableNode[]) defaults. Jacobian carries a
    Unicode toString() while typeset() stays LaTeX.
  * Extract MuntzPadeFunction; RiccatiMittagLefflerFunction extends it,
    implements ComplexFunction, and derives evaluation order from bits.
    Fluent shape on padePolynomials, muntzCoefficientsAtV, solveHankel.
    Cache lifecycle split: clearCache drops references, disposeCache
    closes native; invalidateCache override drops the Padé cache and
    α-vector.
  * partialDerivativeWithRespectToV rewritten to use p.derivative("v"),
    q.derivative("v"), r.derivative("v") directly, registered under
    p_dv, q_dv, r_dv on the shared Context so the bytecode field
    descriptors L<name>; resolve to the actual loaded classes on the
    shared ExpressionClassLoader. JacobianAtVTest green at all three
    closed-form pins (w₁=1/Γ(1.6), w₂=1.5/Γ(2.2), w₃=1.25/Γ(2.8)); full
    suite 780/780 in ~8s.
  * Confine fat-jar shading to the -Pdebian profile so the development
    build is unaffected.
  * Bundle JavaFX inside the shaded fat jar; strip --add-opens javafx.*
    flags from installed wrappers; add arb.applications.Launcher to
