    6594908; restore per-row progress meter to System.out; drop FFT
    cross-check overlays from sampler chart build.
  * Drop the Known Test Failures section from README.
  * Strip apostrophes from comments inside install-bin.sh awk block.
  * Riemann–Liouville fractional integral I^μ as a first-class symbolic
    operator. New RiemannLiouvilleFractionalIntegralNode mirrors the
    Caputo derivative node: parser keyword fracint, full AST surgery
    semantics (accept, dependsOn, differentiate, integral=I^(μ+1),
    spliceInto, type, typeset LaTeX, toString Unicode), and a generic
    integrand-based bytecode generation path. Closed-form short-circuit
    overrides on VariableNode, ExponentiationNode (t^β →
    Γ(β+1)/Γ(β+μ+1)·t^(β+μ)), AdditionNode, NegationNode,
    MultiplicationNode (constant·f), DivisionNode (f/constant),
    LiteralConstantNode (c·t^μ/Γ(μ+1)), FunctionNode (inline body),
    and the Riemann–Liouville node itself (semigroup
    I^μ∘I^ν = I^(μ+ν)).
  * Inverse identity D^μ[I^μ f] = f verified at non-integer μ on
    multiple test functions at 256 bits. Volterra residual test on a
    Müntz partial sum (qrh.tex Test 1) shows the first non-vanishing
    coefficient at t^((N+1)μ) equals −a_{N+1}(v).
  * Wrapper RiemannLiouvilleFractionalIntegralNode exposes its
    closedFormResult through hasClosedFormFractionalDerivative and
    fractionalDerivative so the closed-form path is reachable from the
    parent Caputo node.
  * ConstantCoefficientFractionalRiccatiEquation reduced to a
    deprecated stub that redirects to RiccatiMittagLefflerFunction.
  * Expression.context encapsulated: field is now private with a
    getContext()/setContext() pair (getContext lazy-constructs a
    Context if absent), the bytecode-emitted context field on
    generated classes carries ACC_PROTECTED, and Context.setFieldValue
    falls back to getDeclaredField+setAccessible to remain reflective
    against the tightened access. All in-tree callers migrated to
    getContext() across 11 files.
  * Parser arrow normalization widened: ➜, ↦, ⟶, ⟼ all fold to ➔ at
    the lexer stage so all arrow variants parse identically.
  * Generic Jacobian class on the Function interface (#991): the
    jacobian(String[])/jacobian(VariableReference[])/jacobian(
    VariableNode[]) defaults on Function build a Jacobian<D,R,F>
    instance whose closure under self-application yields Hessians for
    free; closes #991 Phase 1.
  * Closes: #984, #991. Test suite 786/786 green.
  * Expression.shouldCache enables peek/poke memoization for generated
    functionals (#993). The !isGeneratedFunctional() clause is dropped
    so integer-domain sequences whose codomain is a function type now
    receive the integer-keyed TreeMap memo. generateCachePeek and
    generateCachePokeEpilogue gain functional-codomain branches: peek
    returns the cached function reference directly (no result.set, no
    out-parameter aliasing); poke dups the function instance left on
    the stack by generateFunctionalElement, pokes it under k, and
    returns it (no <init>, no set). Function references are immutable
    handles, so the deep-copy-on-hit dance used for value-type
    codomains is skipped. The Müntz–Padé recurrence
    a:k➔v➔…·a(k-1)(v)+r(v)·S(k)(v),
    S:k➔v➔sum(j➔a(j)(v)·a(k-1-j)(v){j=1..k-2}) drops from O(M³) to
    O(M²) per v.
  * MuntzPadeFunction.solveHankel: Padé numerator built from the
    compiled functional n➔a(n)+sum(j➔q[j]·a(n-j){j=1..n-1}) (#990
    step 3 redo with the q[j] component-access bracket form);
    DiagonalPade encapsulates the (P,Q) pair and its sub-Context
    lifecycle (#990 step 2); HankelSystem extracts the Hankel
    coefficient linear solve into arb.solvers (#990 step 1); dead
    pz/qz scratch dropped from evaluatePadeAtCachedOrder (#990 step
    4); try-with-resources on H, neg_b, qMat in solveHankel.
  * Auto-curry parser shapes (#975). Expression accepts
    (p₁,…,pₙ)=body and name(p₁,…,pₙ)=body as declaration
    forms equivalent to the chain p₁➔p₂➔…➔pₙ➔body, and
    f(a₁,…,aₙ) at any call site as equivalent to the chained
    application f(a₁)(a₂)…(aₙ). parseExplicitInputVariableIfPresent
    recognises the new shapes, returns the first parameter name, and
    stashes the remainder in pendingParameterList; parseInputVariableAssignment
    drains that list by recursing into the cloned sub-expression, producing
    an AST byte-for-byte equal to the equivalent arrow chain. The
    outer-level evaluateOptionalIndependentVariableSpecification routes
    to parseInputVariableAssignment when parameters remain, and
    parse(boolean) skips the redundant resolve() when rootNode is
    already populated. resolvePostfixOperators's '(' branch reads the
    comma-separated argument list and folds it into nested
    FunctionalEvaluationNodes; the reified-functional domain promotion
    is exposed as the new public static helper
    FunctionalEvaluationNode.promoteDomainToScalarOfReifiedFunctional
    and invoked once before the first argument so P(3)(x) continues to
    work. AutoCurryTest pins the equivalences over rootNode.toString().
  * CachedNode.accept descends into the delegate so nested StaticNodes
    inside SharedNodes are visible to nodeStream; fixes the t/(2·π)
    NaN that surfaced in ceil(√(t/(2·π)))-floor(√(t/(2·π))) when
    common-subexpression elimination buried the (2·π) StaticNode under
    a SharedNode delegate. SharedNode overrides so only the canonical
    instance descends. SharedNodeStaticHoistingTest pins the regression.
  * LogGammaJetNode and FunctionNode typeset lnΓ with auto-sizing \left
    … \right delimiters.
  * Closes: #975, #990, #993. Test suite 805/805 green on JDK 26.

